Dear Uti,

I'm sorry that I can't visit you as often as I could, even when I know that I should've.
I'm truly thankful that I've had you as my grandma.
I'm thankful of the times I've spent with you all this years.
When you nurtured me.
When you spoil me as how grandmothers would usually do to their grandchildrens.
You devoted your life to help others and contribute to the society by being an awesome doctor.

The point is I'll truly miss your presence in my life, but I know you're in a happier place now and that you're reunited with Akung :) Watch me closely from above Uti, I'll make you proud

From your most handsome grandson, Audy.
